label: Hypoxia

label: Lowest O2 level
definition: Oxygen saturation was measured at admission, 24-hour follow-up, and 48-hour follow-up timepoints and only collected for cases. Cases with oxygen saturation measured while on oxygen are categorized with those who had an oxygen saturation 61-91%. Oxygen saturation categories are decreased by 2% for sites at a higher altitude (Zambia and South Africa).

Oxygen saturation categories are decreased by 2% for sites are higher altitude (Zambia and South Africa).
